The psychology of auctioning too much: why spend more money?
Buyers' auctions are likely to spend more, to overestimate the goods.
Neurologists and economists researchers from the University of New York have been able to discover the neuro-economic bases of this known and apparently irrational behavior.
According to their study on the journal Science men do not want to stay back in a race like eBay auction, so they are available to pay even a higher price.
The research tried to trace the nervous scheme of this "partite" at the level of the nervous system through experimental auctions.
One group of volunteers played the lot, the other group of players participated in a auction while with the method of functional magnetic resonance imaging (fMRI) examined the active areas of the brain of the people participating in the experiment.
In both games the participants could win money, but in the auction game, in which the substantial element is to bid more than the other, the body lying beneath the cerebral cortex gets into effect intensively when you lose the game.
This brain area, in addition to other functions, plays a role in the autogratification mechanism of the nervous system.
Therefore, according to researchers, the price rise is explained by the scanning of the vehement reaction of the stratified body.
To support their theory, the economists of the research group carried out a financial follow-up survey.
In this investigation three groups have bidred against a partner under different conditions.
The control group reported the actual value of the product in question and they did their bet.
To another group besides this they promised that in the event of winning, they would receive another $15 prize.
The third group would have received $15 before the auction, but the group members would have lost the money in the event of auction loss.
The difference between the two groups consisted of the fact that one of them was highlighted as winning, while the other was losing.
Checking the hypothesis of neurologists, the members of the group who played "against loss" were willing to make higher bets of the control group or "winner".
"These results are not deductible from any of the previously existing economic theories.
In fact, these so far explained the phenomena found in auctions with the joy of winning and avoiding risk.
Only the methods of creating the neurological image have helped resolve the contradiction between the two theories, so that we have come to a third explanation" - said Andrew Schutter, professor of the Faculty of Economics of the University of New York.
Hepatitis: when do you contact your doctor?
Nearly half a billion people in the world suffer from chronic hepatitis B or C, in Hungary instead of the first causes of death, chronic liver diseases are mentioned.
In Hungary the number of hepatitis patients amounts to one hundred thousand, of which only 7000 are cured: the reason is that many patients do not know how to be infected.
The definition of hepatitis is the collective name of the contagious liver disease caused by several viruses.
There are many similarities between the symptoms, typical are hepatitis and itteritis, but their pathogens and the diseases caused differ from one another.
Hepatitis viruses are spread in two main forms depending on the pathogen: hepatitis A and E via the food channel (e.g. water and infected foods), hepatitis B, C, D and other viruses with blood and organic liquids (sperm, vaginal loss, saliva).
For travellers it is useful to vaccinate against virus A and B, against C there is no vaccine.
The symptoms of hepatitis A appear two to three weeks after the consumption of infected foods, accompanied by general malaise, weakness, abdominal pain and nausea.
After yellow spots are formed on the skin and on the white of the eyes, the faeces become clear and the dark urine, healing occurs within two to three weeks.
One million people die every year worldwide for hepatitis B, the most serious variant of the disease, which causes liver cancer and liver cirrhosis.
The main reason for this is, according to estimates, that only one person in ten receives pharmacological treatment.
Hepatitis C can also have very serious consequences: if it is not cured it can cause liver cirrhosis and liver tumors.
Most infected people do not know that they have contracted the disease because pathogens subdly destroy liver cells, in many cases the first symptoms appear after 20-30 years.
Therefore it is very important to prevent and perform regular medical tests.
This disease is much more frequent than the average in three groups: those who had a blood transfusion before 1991, drug addicts and tattoos.
In the world today, the number of people infected with chronic hepatitis C virus amounts to 200 million.
As a routine laboratory examination also reveals the disease, it is worth contacting your family doctor when you notice any symptoms of unknown origin.
Recognized in time the disease is cureable, the virus can be eliminated by the body, so the infectious power ceases and the formation of tumors can be prevented.
September 30th is the World Day of Hepatitis, organized for the first time in 2004 worldwide by sick associations.
The aim is to draw attention to chronic viral hepatitis, the causes of its development and early recognition of the disease.
Who believes in God feels less pain?
According to the result of a recent survey religious faith works as a kind of analgesic that has made the death of Catholic martyrs more bearable.
The scientists at Oxford University conducted an interesting experiment, examining how faith in God influences the feeling of pain, the British Telegraph reported.
In the context of the somewhat bizarre investigation, an electroshock was carried out with 12 Catholic believers and as many atheists, while everyone watched a painting depicting the Virgin Mary.
On the basis of the results, Catholic believers were able to reject much of the pain.
Thanks to the exploratory technique of the human brain it was discovered that Catholics were able to activate the part of the brain responsible for pain control.
The test is the first of a series of research in which scientists, philosophers and theologians from other academics are also involved.
The test was done exactly like this: an instrument that emits discharges and passes the electroshock was connected to the left hand of the subject of the experiment.
The researchers asked the participants to focus on two paintings, the virgin Mary painted in the XVII century by Sassoferrato and the Lady with the hermellin of Leonardo da Vinci painted in the XV century.
The authors of the examination hoped that the image of the virgin Mary originated a sort of religious state among the believers, while the painting of Leonardo was chosen because it did not differ too much from the other and considered it to be of reassuring effect.
The experiment participants spent half an hour in front of the MRI scanner and in this time area received 20 electroshocks in four consecutive series, while observing either the religious or the other painting.
The Catholics reported that the vision of the virgin Mary made them feel "safe", as if "someone took care" of them and "they calmed down and were pervading by peace".
By looking at the image on religious subjects, they found 12% less pain than they had before them the work of Leonardo.
The psychologist Miguel Farias, who took part in the test himself, believes that such a result can be achieved with any image from the strong effect even for atheists, however, it is necessary to find the appropriate image.
